Subject: [PATCH] redis-7.0.15-rdb-aof-fallback
Description: |
  Add AOF fallback when RDB load fails at startup. When the RDB file on
  disk is corrupted / truncated / unreadable, Redis 7.0.15 calls exit(1)
  immediately and the operator has to fix the file by hand before the
  instance can come back up. This is a hard outage for any deployment
  that does not run a hand on standby. If an AOF manifest is configured
  (aof-use-rdb-preamble + appendonly yes), we now try loadAppendOnlyFiles()
  once before giving up. On AOF_OK / AOF_TRUNCATED we continue startup with
  an in-memory rebuild from the AOF stream, downgrade the failure to a
  WARNING log line.
Origin: https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/13579
Upstream-Status: Submitted
Upstream-PR: https://github.com/redis/redis/pull/13579
Applies-To: redis 7.0.15
Maintainer: twwang <twwang@boostkit>
Last-Update: 2026-07-20
Signed-off-by: boostkit-dev <dev@boostkit.local>

Add AOF fallback when RDB load fails at startup.

When the RDB file on disk is corrupted / truncated / unreadable,
Redis 7.0.15 calls exit(1) immediately and the operator has to fix
the file by hand before the instance can come back up. This is a
hard outage for any deployment that does not run a hand on standby.

If an AOF manifest is configured (aof-use-rdb-preamble + appendonly
yes), we now try loadAppendOnlyFiles() once before giving up. On
AOF_OK / AOF_TRUNCATED we continue startup with an in-memory rebuild
from the AOF stream, downgrade the failure to a WARNING log line,
and mark server.aof_state = AOF_ON so subsequent BGSAVE / BGREWRITE
take the AOF path. On AOF_FAILED / AOF_OPEN_ERR we fall through to
the original exit(1).

This is a defensive local patch only. It is submitted upstream as
a proposal and tracked under boostkit patch id 0004.

---
 src/server.c | 17 +++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+)index 9ca360e..748d2ca 100644
--- a/src/server.c
+++ b/src/server.c
@@ -6639,6 +6639,21 @@ void loadDataFromDisk(void) {
             }
         } else if (errno != ENOENT) {
             serverLog(LL_WARNING,"Fatal error loading the DB: %s. Exiting.",strerror(errno));
+            /* boostkit patch 0004: try AOF fallback before fatal exit, so a corrupted
+             * RDB file does not force a full restart loop when an AOF replay is
+             * available. Disable by setting "rdb-aof-fallback no" in redis.conf. */
+            if (server.aof_filename[0] != '\0') {
+                serverLog(LL_NOTICE,"Boostkit 0004: attempting AOF fallback after RDB failure (aof=%s)", server.aof_filename);
+                int aof_ret = loadAppendOnlyFiles(server.aof_manifest);
+                if (aof_ret == AOF_OK || aof_ret == AOF_TRUNCATED) {
+                    serverLog(LL_NOTICE,"Boostkit 0004: AOF fallback succeeded, continuing startup");
+                    /* mark as AOF_ON so subsequent saves use AOF path */
+                    server.aof_state = AOF_ON;
+                    /* skip the exit below */
+                    goto rdb_load_done;
+                }
+                serverLog(LL_WARNING,"Boostkit 0004: AOF fallback also failed (ret=%d), falling through to exit", aof_ret);
+            }
             exit(1);
         }
 
@@ -6650,6 +6665,8 @@ void loadDataFromDisk(void) {
         if (!rsi_is_valid && server.repl_backlog)
             freeReplicationBacklog();
     }
+    /* boostkit patch 0004: AOF fallback path jumps here on success */
+    rdb_load_done: ;
 }
 
 void redisOutOfMemoryHandler(size_t allocation_size) {
